  <para>The <emphasis role="bold"><!-- DNT-Start -->LENGTH<!-- DNT-End --> </emphasis>function returns the
  length of the string resulting from the <emphasis>expression</emphasis> by
  treating the <emphasis>expression </emphasis>as a temporary <!-- DNT-Start -->STRING<!-- DNT-End -->.</para>

  <para>Example:</para>

  <!-- DNT-Start --><programlisting>INTEGER MyLength := LENGTH('XYZ' + 'ABC');
      //MyLength is 6</programlisting><!-- DNT-End -->

  <para>See Also: <link linkend="String_Operators">String Operators</link>, <link linkend="STRING"><!-- DNT-Start -->STRING<!-- DNT-End --></link></para>
</sect1>
